First, we extract the necessary values from the provided statements.

Step 1. Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, the only liabilities shown are current liabilities.  
  Total Liabilities = Total Current Liabilities = 8,028,630.43  
  Total Owner's Equity = 31,744,117.89  
Thus, Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity  
  = 8,028,630.43 / 31,744,117.89  
  ≈ 0.25  

Step 2. Calculate Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement:  
  Net Profit = 3,744,117.89  
  Total Revenue = 28,572,608.70  
Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (3,744,117.89 / 28,572,608.70) × 100  
  ≈ 13.11%  

Step 3. Calculate Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
• From the cash flow statement:  
  Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -10,442,735.47  
• From the balance sheet:  
  Total Current Liabilities = 8,028,630.43  
Thus, Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities  
  = -10,442,735.47 / 8,028,630.43  
  ≈ -1.30  

Now, we present the answers in the required JSON format.

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.25",
    "Net Profit Margin": "13.11%",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-1.30"
  }
}
